# Add Semantic VAD Support to IGOOR (Revised Plan)

Fresh branch from `master` — the old `01.5.3-semantic-vad-in-preflow` branch is abandoned.

## Overview

When `continuous` mode is active, VAD detects speech-end events and sends audio for transcription. After transcription, a **lightweight semantic VAD** LLM call decides whether the speaker has finished talking (`"ok"`) or not (`"nok"`). If `"nok"`, the system stays in listening mode and waits for more speech. If `"ok"` (or if `always_generate` is enabled), the normal flow pipeline runs.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The existing [preflow](file:///c:/AIKU/experiments/igoor/plugins/flow/flow.py#203-233) remains untouched.** Semantic VAD is an independent, minimal LLM call that runs *before* preflow. It only answers "ok/nok" — it doesn't extract theme, timeframe, or memory type.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Prompt design: with or without few-shot examples?**
> The proposed prompt below is intentionally minimal. I recommend adding **2-3 very short** examples to reduce ambiguity, especially edge cases like single-word utterances ("Oui") or trailing connectors ("parce que..."). Even small models benefit from 2-3 examples for binary classification. My recommendation:
> ```
> Exemples:
> Q: "Qu'est-ce que tu veux manger ce" → "nok"
> Q: "Qu'est-ce que tu veux manger ce soir ?" → "ok"
> Q: "Je voulais te dire que..." → "nok"
> Q: "Bonjour !" → "ok"
> ```
> Let me know if you prefer zero-shot or this short few-shot approach.

> [!WARNING]
> **Audio accumulation when semantic VAD returns "nok":** When the VAD detects speech-end but semantic VAD says "nok", should the frontend:
> - **(A)** Keep accumulating raw audio and re-transcribe the entire combined audio on next VAD trigger? (Higher accuracy, growing latency)
> - **(B)** Append only the new text server-side to the existing transcription? (Lower latency, possible transcription discontinuities)
>
> The plan below implements **(A)** by default (matching the old branch approach). Please confirm.

> [!NOTE]
> **`continuous` setting already exists** in [asrjs/settings.json](file:///c:/AIKU/experiments/igoor/plugins/asrjs/settings.json) (line 3, default `false`). It is read on mount. The toggle button in the template will be **removed** — continuous mode is switched via settings UI only (to be built later). The mic button is always clickable and starts the active mode.

