### Component 4: Semantic VAD Prompts

#### [MODIFY] [prompts.yaml (fr_FR)](file:///c:/AIKU/experiments/igoor/plugins/flow/locales/fr_FR/prompts.yaml)

Append a new `semantic_vad` key after the existing [preflow](file:///c:/AIKU/experiments/igoor/plugins/flow/flow.py#203-233) section:

```yaml
semantic_vad:
  system: |
    Tu reçois une conversation en cours entre un interlocuteur (Q) et l'utilisateur (R).
    Agis comme un VAD sémantique: si la question de Q est terminée, réponds "ok", autrement "nok".

    Exemples:
    Q: "Qu'est-ce que tu veux manger ce" → "nok"
    Q: "Qu'est-ce que tu veux manger ce soir ?" → "ok"
    Q: "Je voulais te dire que..." → "nok"
    Q: "Bonjour !" → "ok"
```

#### [MODIFY] [prompts.yaml (en_EN)](file:///c:/AIKU/experiments/igoor/plugins/flow/locales/en_EN/prompts.yaml)

Same, in English:

```yaml
semantic_vad:
  system: |
    You receive an ongoing conversation between an interlocutor (Q) and the user (R).
    Act as a semantic VAD: if Q's question/statement is complete, respond "ok", otherwise "nok".

    Examples:
    Q: "What do you want to eat" → "nok"
    Q: "What do you want to eat tonight?" → "ok"
    Q: "I wanted to tell you that..." → "nok"
    Q: "Hello!" → "ok"
```

